On Saturday night, a taxi from Gauteng was travelling from a funeral at Ematimatolo back to Joburg when it was ambushed by a group of shooters in Kwazulu-Natal. A total of 11 people were killed and only two survived without any injuries. The incident occured along the R74 road between Colenso and Weenen, The attackers emerged from bushes near the road, before opening fire on the vehicle's occupants. The victims were allegedly from a taxi association in Gauteng and had come to attend the funeral of one of their members. Police have implemented a 72-hour action plan to trace and arrest the suspects. 